Brand new ground floor 131sqm strata offices has exclusive alfresco areas and 3 basement car bays.

Inner metropolitan fringe CBD location 3kms* west of Perth GPO and within walking distance to the Subiaco town centre and only 200m* from the West Leederville Train Station* approx.

This office presents to a high standard and is air-conditioned, has suspended t-bar ceilings with flush lighting, is painted & carpeted throughout, comes self contained having a built in kitchenette, toilet & hand basin facilities, has an efficient office layout and takes advantage of excellent natural lighting with superb elevated aspects fronting Northwood Street.

To obtain further information and to arrange for an inspection please contact - Michael Milne on M: 0403 466 603, P: 9320 0040 or michael.milne@cbre.com.au

The West Leederville strip is undergoing a vibrant revitalisation with the likes of Mary Street Bakery, Myrtle Ivy and Hylin adding amenity and high quality F&B options. Besk, beer café and restaurant is due to open two doors down from this retail opportunity in early 2018.  

West Leederville is benefiting from a significant number of apartment developments occurring in close proximity to the train station. 256-258 Railway Parade is a freestanding character building located across from the West Leederville train station. 

Suit a variety of uses including:
- Cafe
- Showroom
- Offices
- Medical
- Gym
- Warehouse with rear lane access and roller door is available independently of the main premises

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Refurbished two level character office available for lease in a great location.

Features high ceilings, large offices, polished floor boards and fire places.

Superbly located on the corner of Railway Parade and Kimberley Street, 200m from the West Leederville train station.

Suit medical or office usage.

Area: 170sqm
Rent: $375/sqm net plus outgoings
2 secure undercover car bays at $250 per bay pcm and 4 open bays at $150 per bay pcm.

For further information or to arrange an inspection please contact Luke Bray 0403 184 340.

23 Oxford Close presents an outstanding opportunity to acquire a superbly located showroom/office building, with ultra-high end fit out in place, which also offers considerable redevelopment potential.

The well-presented 669sqm*, two storey building sits on a rectangular 972sqm* land parcel and is provided with dual, 20m access across both front and rear.

Located in the 'Southport Street Node Activity Centre', 8 levels of retail, office and residential is allowable under current zoning.  Oxford Close is nominated as the street in which 'active retail frontages are to be concentrated' under the City of Cambridge, West Leederville Activity Centre Plan.

Below we highlight key property features:

- Attractive contemporary building with a high quality, modern fit-out and tremendous natural light via a central louvered atrium
- 16 onsite car bays (5 under cover)
- 20m frontage to Oxford Close, 20m frontage to Mullane Lane
- Located centrally to the active and rapidly transforming ‘Southport Street Node’ precinct
- Significant street presence and signage opportunities
- Excellent access to public transport with free-to-ride Green Cat bus service 200m* from the building providing linkage to the CBD
- Direct and convenient access to Kwinana, Mitchell and Graham Farmer Freeways and 310m* to City West train station
- Redevelopment strongly supported by the West Leederville activity Centre Plan 2017, which allows for construction of up to 8 storeys, with minimal set backs on the site.
- Activated street with numerous café’s and amenities close by complimented by ample street parking

The property is being offered for sale via Offers to Purchase invited, closing Wednesday 15th May 2019 at 2pm AWST.
